com.sana.android.plugin.data.listener

Interface DataListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataChunkListener, DataChunkListenerForTest, MockListener, TimedListener, TimedListenerForTest

    public interface DataListener
    The interface that can be added to BaseDataEvent implementations.

    • Method Detail

      • startListening

        void startListening()
        Called by the library user after the app is ready to receive data from the event.

      • stopListening

        void stopListening()
        Called by the library user after the app no longer needs data updates. This moethod or stopListening(long, java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit) must be called in order to prevent resource leak.

      • setExpectedSender

        void setExpectedSender(java.lang.Object sender)
        Called by the library user to tell the event from which object this listener is expecting data updates.This should always be one of the GeneralDevice implementations. So if you are using CaptureManager, the sender should be captureManager.getDevice();
        Parameters:
        sender - The source of data update.

      • getExpectedSender

        java.lang.Object getExpectedSender()
        Get the expected sender object set by setExpectedSender(Object).
        Returns:
        The expected sender set by setExpectedSender(Object).

      • stopListening

        void stopListening(long timeout,
                   java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit unit)
        Called by the library user after the app no longer needs data updates. Explicit timeout is needed in case the disposal of resources takes too much time.
        Parameters:
        timeout -
        unit -

      • putData

        void putData(java.lang.Object[] data)
        Called by the data event to put data into the listener. This is the notification from the event. Note that the data passed in will be the original data object. Therefore you should never modify the object itself in case there are other listeners receiving the same data. Make a copy if you really need to make some changes to it.
        Parameters:
        data - The data update.

      • processData

        void processData(java.lang.Object sender,
                 java.lang.Object[] data)
        Called by the library user to process the given data.
        Parameters:
        sender - The source of the data.
        data - The given data.
